00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:45,587
THE CHARACTERS, INSTITUTIONS
COMPANIES, AND PLACES

2
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:48,006
DEPICTED IN THIS DRAMA
ARE ENTIRELY FICTIONAL

3
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,260
The child

4
00:00:53,636 --> 00:00:54,971
your father saved.

5
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,102
That was me.

6
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,422
What

7
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,425
are you talking about?

8
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:37,055
In the apartment I lived in,

9
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:40,809
there was a big fire.

10
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:45,063
The door to my room was blocked,
so I couldn't escape.

11
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:47,649
Someone came to save me.

12
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:51,736
Before the building collapsed,

13
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:55,657
he handed me over to the firefighters…

14
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:04,999
He saved my life.

15
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:10,004
So I had been searching for his family.

16
00:02:11,297 --> 00:02:13,174
I recently found out his name.

17
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:20,348
Mr. Kang Kyung-tae.

18
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:36,865
Are you sure?

19
00:02:40,702 --> 00:02:42,620
Did you really verify it?

20
00:02:44,414 --> 00:02:45,957
It doesn't make sense.

21
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:50,837
How could you…

22
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,006
How…

23
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:57,594
That's impossible.

24
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,270
I need some time alone.

25
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:11,232
You should go.

26
00:03:38,968 --> 00:03:41,054
Why is it you of all people?

27
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:41,971
Why?

28
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:44,098
I resented my dad so much.

29
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:47,685
I hated him so much.

30
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:49,646
I wish

31
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,774
you hadn't told me.

32
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,569
You should've kept me in the dark.

33
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:10,083
How will I…

34
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:13,461
I…

35
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:22,262
How am I supposed to
look at you from now on?

36
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:36,878
<i>I will wait</i>

37
00:05:36,961 --> 00:05:39,130
<i>until you had enough time to think.</i>

38
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:53,478
I WILL WAIT UNTIL YOU HAD
ENOUGH TIME TO THINK.

39
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:10,244
Why are you wearing sunglasses
all of a sudden?

40
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:11,913
Did you get a stye?

41
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:13,206
The sun is strong today.

42
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,835
What? It's awfully cloudy.

43
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:19,837
Eun-ho.

44
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:20,755
Eun-ho?

45
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,215
Can I have a minute with you?

46
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:23,925
Okay.

47
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,891
A month?

48
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:34,435
I knew you wouldn't be worried about it.

49
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:37,271
You've been too busy dating
that you lost track of time.

50
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:40,316
We agreed on six months at the beginning.

51
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:42,527
So you have a little more than a month.

52
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:45,113
You might need
some time to think about it.

53
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:46,823
That's why I brought it up early.

54
00:06:49,408 --> 00:06:51,077
I see. Thank you.

55
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:54,997
We also agreed that
you could look for another job.

56
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:58,626
Don't hesitate to let me know
if you want to change jobs.

57
00:06:58,709 --> 00:06:59,919
Of course,

58
00:07:00,002 --> 00:07:03,005
I'd love to make you stay
and keep working with you.

59
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,423
That's only what I want.

60
00:07:05,007 --> 00:07:07,385
Discuss it with Ji-yun before deciding.

61
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,431
Okay.

62
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:14,600
I'll think about it and let you know.

63
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,103
Gosh.

64
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:19,856
Ji-yun might not want
to stay away from you.

65
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,607
She might keep you working here.

66
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:24,485
Let me know when you're ready.

67
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:34,829
This is Jang Seo-young
with a background in law.

68
00:07:34,912 --> 00:07:36,998
After working at Seoul
Central District Prosecutors' Office,

69
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,833
she was on the legal team
at Haeseon Electronics.

70
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:41,335
Currently, she's the CEO at an IT company.

71
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:44,005
She's known for her expertise
in risk management.

72
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,049
The last candidate is Oh Min-seok.

73
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,885
After studying law,

74
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:51,929
he was certified as a lawyer
at Herald Law School.

75
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:55,349
After working in mergers and acquisitions
at a major law firm in Korea,

76
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:58,519
he became the youngest CEO
at a game company three years ago.

77
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,772
All of them
fit the requirements we wanted.

78
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:04,609
Let's meet them individually.

79
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:07,153
Mr. Yu, please arrange the meetings.

80
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,825
Yes, ma'am.

81
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:14,368
Meeting's over.

82
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:15,786
Meeting's over.

83
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,079
Good job, everyone.

84
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:21,459
KANG JI-YUN, CEO

85
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:41,163
Jeong-nam.

86
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,248
Oh, Mr. Kim!

87
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:43,249
Over here.

88
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,042
You got much younger than before.

89
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:47,837
From afar, I thought
you were a college student.

90
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,839
That must be why
people were staring at me.

91
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:51,757
- Sit down.
- Please have a seat.

92
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,761
- You grilled the meat so well.
- Thank you.

93
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,513
How have you been?

94
00:09:57,597 --> 00:10:00,891
When you left the company like that,
I felt terrible.

95
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:02,852
Actually,

96
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:05,896
I'm in a different field now.

97
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:09,442
It wasn't the right fit for me.

98
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:13,029
I'm being trained at a small company
someone referred me to.

99
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:14,322
Really?

100
00:10:14,905 --> 00:10:16,574
Where you work isn't important.

101
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:18,701
What matters is that you're working.

102
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:20,453
Have a drink.

103
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:22,705
- Let me serve you first.
- Okay.

104
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:23,748
It's been so long.

105
00:10:23,831 --> 00:10:25,207
Thank you for your time.

106
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,667
I'm the one who's thankful.

107
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,127
- Let me pour you one.
- Okay.

108
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:31,047
How about you?

109
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,757
Are you still busy these days?

110
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:36,510
I read that Peoplez is in charge
of finding a CEO for NEXT.

111
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:37,553
Well, yes.

112
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:40,514
Things are still going well at Peoplez.

113
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:42,850
Have you started searching for candidates?

114
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:45,519
We wouldn't be Peoplez
if we were still searching.

115
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:47,521
- We started contacting our candidates.
- Already?

116
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:48,439
Yeah.

117
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:51,817
Ms. Kang works insanely fast.

118
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:52,818
She isn't just fast.

119
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:56,030
She's one step ahead of anyone else.

120
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:57,657
- It's surprising.
- Really?

121
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,075
Even this time,

122
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:00,868
instead of those formerly in management,

123
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:02,870
people like lawyers and journalists

124
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:03,871
Such candidates…

125
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:09,835
No, I can't. It's a trade secret.

126
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:13,214
A trade secret?

127
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:14,799
Sure, that's important!

128
00:11:19,053 --> 00:11:20,137
Hello, Ms. Kim.

129
00:11:20,221 --> 00:11:22,181
Peoplez is contacting those

130
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:25,017
with a legal or journalist background
instead of managers.

131
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,311
- Are you sure this time?
- <i>Yes, I'm sure.</i>

132
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:29,897
I heard it directly
from a Peoplez employee.

133
00:11:31,690 --> 00:11:35,111
From Peoplez's database that you have,

134
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:37,988
bring me a list of lawyers and journalists

135
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:39,615
that Kang Ji-yun would contact.

136
00:11:39,698 --> 00:11:41,742
Don't forget that this is
your last chance.

137
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:50,626
I would be so scared to be your enemy.

138
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:54,588
You must dislike Ms. Kang so much
for you to attack her

139
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:56,757
from all directions.

140
00:11:56,841 --> 00:12:01,137
I mean, is what we're doing not enough?

141
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,721
If I'm taking it away from her,

142
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:04,640
I shouldn't leave her a single crumb.

143
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,268
Is everything going smoothly?

144
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:08,602
Of course.

145
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:11,439
There can't be any problem.
A lot of money is at stake.

146
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:26,871
Please come in.

147
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:29,748
Hello, I'm from Ikonic Biotechnology.

148
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,709
I'm CEO Park Young-min.

149
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:34,170
- Nice to meet you. I'm Kang Ji-yun.
- Yes.

150
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,629
- Please have a seat.
- Okay.

151
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,760
Wow, I like your office.

152
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,138
You're impressive.

153
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:47,475
Everyone talked about Peoplez
when they recommended me search firms.

154
00:12:47,558 --> 00:12:50,478
I heard that you're also in charge
of finding a CEO for NEXT.

155
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:51,854
Rumors spread fast.

156
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:55,441
You must be busy,
but please help us out too.

157
00:12:55,524 --> 00:12:57,151
We're nowhere near NEXT,

158
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:59,612
but many want to invest in us
for our technology development.

159
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:01,530
Things are going well for us now.

160
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:04,158
We worked hard for several years
after getting our new drug patented.

161
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:06,535
It's finally happening.

162
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,788
I heard that you'll sign a contract
with a German pharmaceutical company.

163
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:12,416
Yes, since then,
we've been getting investment offers.

164
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,876
We've been very busy.

165
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,544
Our investment consultant told us

166
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:18,547
that stabilizing the company is important
at a time like this.

167
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:20,299
Before our new drug gets commercialized,

168
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,551
we plan to focus on development.

169
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,137
Please recommend us competent researchers.

170
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,139
Sure.

171
00:13:42,863 --> 00:13:44,573
Why aren't you going in?

172
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:46,784
Oh, go ahead.

173
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,582
What? Are you alone?

174
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:54,667
Yes, why?

175
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:57,253
Eun-ho left without going in.

176
00:13:58,045 --> 00:13:59,255
Oh, really?

177
00:13:59,338 --> 00:14:01,590
You two are so careful.

178
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:04,677
In case people get suspicious from
seeing you together in the break room?

179
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,722
Have you discussed about his contract?

180
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:10,057
What did you decide?

181
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:12,768
- Contract?
- Yes. Didn't he bring it up?

182
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:15,938
His contract period is almost over,
so I told him to discuss it with you.

183
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:18,899
Oh, is it up already?

184
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,029
Did you fight or something?

185
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,156
Is something wrong?

186
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,118
Mi-ae.

187
00:14:31,245 --> 00:14:32,621
How about some soju with me?

188
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:44,008
How could he

189
00:14:44,091 --> 00:14:46,802
be Eun-ho, of all people?

190
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:50,723
Is this meant to be
or an ill-fated relationship?

191
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,686
Isn't my dad nasty?

192
00:14:57,313 --> 00:14:59,398
What he's done to me was enough.

193
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:03,444
I was trying to live without being lonely.

194
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:07,823
It's about him all over again.

195
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:14,121
So what are you going to do?

196
00:15:23,505 --> 00:15:24,715
Stay with him.

197
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:27,009
What's the problem with staying with him?

198
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,803
To be brutally honest, it isn't
Eun-ho's fault that your dad died.

199
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:35,184
Aren't you glad that
your dad saved Eun-ho?

200
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:42,733
I've been resenting Dad all my life.

201
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:48,322
I still can't understand his choice.

202
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,658
Stop resenting him.

203
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:53,535
Stop hating him.

204
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,709
Seo Mi-ae, how could she?

205
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,020
When you told me…

206
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:06,316
there were two people
who brought you where you are now,

207
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,194
is one of them

208
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,739
my dad?

209
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:19,413
He told me not to give up

210
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:22,791
and survive no matter what.

211
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,712
What your father told me that day

212
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,548
has stayed with me, even now.

213
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:34,386
Whenever I feel like collapsing,

214
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:36,638
I think of his voice and endure.

215
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,017
So that's why I'm here

216
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:42,394
as well as Byeol.

217
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,356
All thanks to him.

218
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:45,707
<i>Ji-yun.</i>

219
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:49,878
Ji-yun.

220
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:54,174
<i>You're number one in my life.</i>

221
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:05,310
<i>Not this one.</i>

222
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:08,939
Not this one.

223
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:12,067
Not this one either.

224
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:16,071
Byeol, which outfit are you looking for?

225
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,948
What you're wearing is pretty too.

226
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:20,659
No, this isn't good enough.

227
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,703
What do you mean?

228
00:19:22,786 --> 00:19:24,413
You look like a princess to me.

229
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:26,248
Princesses don't dress like this.

230
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:31,044
Byeol, clothes aren't important.

231
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,504
You're so beautiful.

232
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:34,131
Let's just go in this outfit.

233
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,216
We're both late.

234
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,177
You only care about work.

235
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,928
- What?
- You have no idea.

236
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,680
I hate you!

237
00:19:41,763 --> 00:19:42,598
But…

238
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:46,310
Byeol.

239
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:48,395
Seol, I love your outfit today.

240
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:49,688
You look like a princess.

241
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:50,898
Thanks.

242
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,108
Byeol.

243
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,652
Is that how you're dressed today?

244
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,905
You don't look like a princess.

245
00:19:57,988 --> 00:19:59,156
Aren't you going to the party today?

246
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:11,460
Ji-young is having
her birthday party today.

247
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:13,712
It's a princess party.

248
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:15,297
I know.

249
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,548
Are you going?

250
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,635
- No, I'm not going.
- Why not?

251
00:20:19,718 --> 00:20:21,428
All the girls are going.

252
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:28,352
That sounds boring.

253
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:30,520
I'm going to go read at Uncle's bookstore.

254
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:32,564
I see.

255
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:48,747
- Kang-seok.
- Hey, Ji-yun.

256
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,168
Sis!

257
00:20:54,002 --> 00:20:55,170
Hi, Byeol.

258
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,130
She must be excited to see you at least.

259
00:20:57,714 --> 00:21:00,550
I don't know what happened,
but she's feeling down today.

260
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,094
It's not what you think.

261
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:04,721
Is that why you've been sighing

262
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:06,515
without reading your favorite books?

263
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,393
What's wrong? Did something bad happen?

264
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,522
Let's talk over there.

265
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:16,066
What? Are you keeping it a secret from me?

266
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:19,319
You're a man, so you won't understand.

267
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:22,531
Gosh, that's making me feel disappointed.

268
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:25,367
Okay, you girls have a deep conversation.

269
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:42,968
