282
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:47,741
Shall we give her the gift?

283
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:56,041
It's so big.

284
00:23:00,712 --> 00:23:01,713
Here's your present.

285
00:23:02,297 --> 00:23:04,257
Thank you for being born, Ji-young.

286
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:05,884
BABY TWINS TWO-STORY HOUSE

287
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:10,180
Thank you, Byeol.

288
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:20,690
Going down!

289
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:36,248
Sis, thank you so much for today.

290
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:37,707
You're the best.

291
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:40,710
There's no need to thank me.
We're friends.

292
00:23:40,794 --> 00:23:43,255
Friends are supposed to help each other.

293
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,465
Feel free to tell me when
something like this happens again.

294
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:46,758
Can I really?

295
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:51,304
Dad doesn't understand this stuff.

296
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,557
That's how dads are.

297
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,100
Was your dad like that too?

298
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,102
Yes.

299
00:23:57,686 --> 00:23:58,937
My dad was worse.

300
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:01,106
He was bad at tying my hair too.

301
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:02,607
- Really?
- Yes.

302
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:03,984
He tied my hair so tight

303
00:24:04,067 --> 00:24:05,527
that he pulled out my hair.

304
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:08,822
He could only tie it up. He didn't know
how to braid my hair like yours.

305
00:24:08,905 --> 00:24:11,324
My dad is really good at tying my hair.

306
00:24:11,408 --> 00:24:13,535
Disco, crisscross, and centipede hair.

307
00:24:13,618 --> 00:24:15,579
He's even good at braiding.

308
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,293
Sis,

309
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:22,836
can I borrow your phone?

310
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:26,006
- My phone?
- I want to call my dad.

311
00:24:26,756 --> 00:24:29,009
I think he might be upset.

312
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:31,761
I told him this morning that I hated him.

313
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:34,347
I want to say sorry.

314
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,799
Dad!

315
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:26,650
- Did you eat something delicious?
- Yes.

316
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:28,526
- Did you have fun?
- Yes.

317
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:34,824
- Dad.
- Yes?

318
00:25:34,908 --> 00:25:37,535
- I missed you.
- You said you hated me this morning.

319
00:25:37,619 --> 00:25:40,580
That's because I like you that much.

320
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:42,249
Because you like me?

321
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:43,667
Sis told me

322
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,169
that you hate them
as much as you like them.

323
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:57,389
MINT CHOCOLATE MILK

324
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:30,839
KANG KYUNG-TAE

325
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:32,590
Dad, I'm here.

326
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:37,053
It took me a long time

327
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,515
getting here.

328
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:00,160
Dad.

329
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:04,247
It's been really difficult for me.

330
00:27:09,627 --> 00:27:11,629
After you passed away,

331
00:27:12,756 --> 00:27:14,716
I didn't know what to do.

332
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:20,513
I hated you so much.

333
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:27,687
I thought it would help me live.

334
00:27:29,647 --> 00:27:31,983
I think I wanted to resent someone.

335
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:41,034
I'm sorry, Dad.

336
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:44,871
Until now,

337
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:48,708
I never smiled at you.

338
00:28:01,304 --> 00:28:02,597
I miss you.

339
00:28:06,434 --> 00:28:07,936
I miss you, Dad.

340
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:38,717
- Hello.
- Hello.

341
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:40,593
