342
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:42,595
Could you hold…

343
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:46,307
<i>Doors are opening.</i>

344
00:28:56,151 --> 00:28:57,444
Why aren't you getting in?

345
00:29:05,452 --> 00:29:06,870
<i>Doors are closing.</i>

346
00:29:25,054 --> 00:29:26,765
Thank you, Eun-ho.

347
00:29:31,853 --> 00:29:32,979
For growing up…

348
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:37,400
to be such a good person.

349
00:29:55,877 --> 00:29:57,337
Aren't you going to hold it?

350
00:30:10,475 --> 00:30:11,684
I will never

351
00:30:13,144 --> 00:30:14,771
let go of this hand.

352
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:18,817
So,

353
00:30:20,026 --> 00:30:21,528
you don't let go either.

354
00:30:27,575 --> 00:30:28,576
Thank you.

355
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:38,670
Let's go, Ms. Kang.

356
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:57,522
Let me check. Hello…

357
00:31:19,711 --> 00:31:20,545
Good morning.

358
00:31:36,102 --> 00:31:37,770
There's no turning back now.

359
00:31:39,022 --> 00:31:40,023
Yes.

360
00:31:40,565 --> 00:31:42,066
That's why I did it.

361
00:32:08,468 --> 00:32:09,802
- Mr. Kim.
- Yes?

362
00:32:09,886 --> 00:32:11,387
A bug might get into your mouth.

363
00:32:12,096 --> 00:32:13,848
I never imagined it.

364
00:32:13,932 --> 00:32:16,142
Why? How could they?

365
00:32:16,225 --> 00:32:17,936
Am I the only one who's in shock?

366
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:19,270
I already knew about it.

367
00:32:19,854 --> 00:32:21,814
Really? I had no idea.

368
00:32:21,898 --> 00:32:22,982
The two of them

369
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:25,693
were pretty bad at hiding it.

370
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:27,904
Yes, I'm back in the office.

371
00:32:27,987 --> 00:32:30,323
I'll call you back after looking it up.

372
00:32:30,406 --> 00:32:31,407
Okay.

373
00:33:29,966 --> 00:33:30,800
Gyu-rim,

374
00:33:30,883 --> 00:33:34,595
you should've reported to me first
after seeing that.

375
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:37,598
- How could you keep it to yourself?
- Should I have spread a rumor?

376
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:39,225
- Give me your hand.
- No.

377
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:43,104
- All of a sudden,
- No.

378
00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:45,231
- Peoplez is full of love.
- No way.

379
00:33:45,314 --> 00:33:46,816
- It's not the right time.
- I mean…

380
00:33:46,899 --> 00:33:48,026
- No.
- It's okay.

381
00:33:48,109 --> 00:33:49,152
No way.

382
00:33:49,235 --> 00:33:50,361
I said it's okay.

383
00:33:54,407 --> 00:33:56,451
Is there someone else dating at work?

384
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:00,663
Don't report things like this.

385
00:34:08,629 --> 00:34:10,882
Kyung-hwa, it was a good time
to tell them.

386
00:34:10,965 --> 00:34:12,592
Are you out of your mind?

387
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:14,093
It's driving me nuts.

388
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:15,887
May I get closer?

389
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:18,431
Yes, hold my hand too.

390
00:34:21,434 --> 00:34:23,519
Kids must not feel hot.

391
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,397
Is Seo-jun's mom not here yet?

392
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:28,066
She must be busy.

393
00:34:28,149 --> 00:34:29,484
His grandma comes more often.

394
00:34:30,526 --> 00:34:31,861
Speaking of Seo-jun,

395
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:34,614
he doesn't seem to take
after his mom, does he?

396
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:36,657
Does he take after his dad?

397
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:38,826
You didn't know?

398
00:34:38,910 --> 00:34:41,829
She isn't Seo-jun's mom by blood.

399
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:44,373
Really? No wonder…

400
00:34:44,457 --> 00:34:45,666
That's why the child is…

401
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,293
What about him?

402
00:34:48,795 --> 00:34:51,255
What's wrong with Seo-jun?

403
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:53,966
It just seems like

404
00:34:54,050 --> 00:34:56,511
there's a certain shadow about him.

405
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:57,553
Shadow, my foot!

406
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,639
There's no child as cheerful as him.

407
00:35:00,223 --> 00:35:04,310
Seo-jun has been loved by his mom
as much as any other kid.

408
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:07,897
Yes, of course. You're right.

409
00:35:19,075 --> 00:35:23,621
Isn't it your son the one
who called us half a family last time?

410
00:35:23,704 --> 00:35:26,124
What would he learn from a mom like you?

411
00:35:26,207 --> 00:35:29,001
Kids can say such things.

412
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:30,378
He apologized enough.

413
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:32,255
There are things that we shouldn't say.

414
00:35:32,338 --> 00:35:34,674
It's a parents' duty to teach their kids.

415
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:37,677
Are you saying that
I didn't educate my child?

416
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:40,054
Giving birth doesn't make
someone a good mom.

417
00:35:40,721 --> 00:35:44,058
Do you even know what my daughter
went through to raise Seo-jun?

418
00:35:45,601 --> 00:35:48,479
Compared to you who talks
about others behind their backs,

419
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:50,857
my daughter is a much better mother.

420
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:53,025
Ma'am, how could you say--

421
00:35:53,109 --> 00:35:54,735
That's enough.

422
00:35:55,570 --> 00:35:57,280
The children might hear you.

423
00:35:58,489 --> 00:36:00,032
Do you want them to find out?

424
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,188
Mom.

425
00:36:30,771 --> 00:36:32,648
Did you have a bad day today?

426
00:36:34,317 --> 00:36:36,527
Why would I have a bad day?

427
00:36:38,571 --> 00:36:41,324
I'm just thinking of Seo-jun.

428
00:36:46,662 --> 00:36:49,624
If he hears that
he doesn't take after his mom,

429
00:36:50,291 --> 00:36:52,376
how terrible would he feel?

430
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:54,003
You said that Seo-jun didn't hear them.

431
00:36:55,296 --> 00:36:57,506
He didn't hear them today,

432
00:36:57,590 --> 00:37:00,051
but he could hear them in the future.

433
00:37:06,515 --> 00:37:07,558
Su-hyeon.

434
00:37:08,142 --> 00:37:09,685
Let's tell Seo-jun the truth.

435
00:37:10,269 --> 00:37:11,103
Mom--

436
00:37:11,187 --> 00:37:14,148
Don't let him find out from someone else.
You tell him first.

437
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:16,692
No matter how much I think about it,
it's for the best.

438
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:17,902
Either way,

439
00:37:18,486 --> 00:37:20,238
he will find out one day.

440
00:37:42,176 --> 00:37:44,220
Why isn't there a picture book today?

441
00:37:44,804 --> 00:37:45,972
Aren't you going to read?

442
00:37:47,598 --> 00:37:49,141
Instead of reading a book,

443
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:51,686
I have something to tell you today.

444
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:52,895
A story?

445
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:54,939
What is it?

446
00:37:58,901 --> 00:38:01,195
Seo-jun, I had

447
00:38:01,696 --> 00:38:02,989
one sister.

448
00:38:03,906 --> 00:38:07,201
She was amazing, pretty, and kind.

449
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:10,037
She was a cheerful person.

450
00:38:10,121 --> 00:38:12,331
She married a wonderful person,

451
00:38:12,415 --> 00:38:14,333
and even had a beautiful baby.

452
00:38:14,917 --> 00:38:16,836
Where is she now?

453
00:38:21,257 --> 00:38:24,593
She's in heaven,
where only good people go.

454
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:26,429
From there,

455
00:38:26,512 --> 00:38:29,557
she's watching over us.

456
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:38,691
The two of them left me a present

457
00:38:38,774 --> 00:38:40,818
so that I wouldn't be lonely.

458
00:38:42,611 --> 00:38:44,071
That present was you.

459
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,411
I have a video.

460
00:38:50,995 --> 00:38:52,246
Do you want to watch it?

461
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:55,416
Okay.

462
00:39:09,347 --> 00:39:10,973
<i>He's so adorable.</i>

463
00:39:11,057 --> 00:39:12,808
- Is that me?
<i>- He's so cute.</i>

464
00:39:12,892 --> 00:39:14,977
<i>He's so beautiful.</i>

465
00:39:15,061 --> 00:39:17,021
<i>- He's so tiny.</i>
- Yes, and

466
00:39:17,104 --> 00:39:19,857
- this is your mom and dad.
<i>- Come and join us.</i>

467
00:39:19,940 --> 00:39:21,442
<i>- Say hello to your aunt.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

468
00:39:21,525 --> 00:39:22,526
<i>Aunt.</i>

469
00:39:23,235 --> 00:39:24,904
- Hello, Seo-jun.
- How cute.

470
00:39:24,987 --> 00:39:26,489
Welcome to our family.

471
00:39:26,572 --> 00:39:28,074
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

472
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:30,409
- Seo-jun.
- What's that?

473
00:39:30,493 --> 00:39:32,620
- He's going to grow a lot.
- Is it tasty?

474
00:39:32,703 --> 00:39:34,372
He can even stand up.

475
00:39:36,290 --> 00:39:37,666
Good job.

476
00:39:38,292 --> 00:39:40,044
- Walk, walk.
- Do you want to go there?

477
00:39:40,127 --> 00:39:41,587
Walk, walk.

478
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:47,927
Let's go to your dad.

479
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:48,844
- Go to your dad.
- Here.

480
00:39:48,928 --> 00:39:50,429
<i>Good boy!</i>

481
00:39:50,513 --> 00:39:52,098
<i>How adorable.</i>

482
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:59,230
It's been a long time
since I saw you as a baby.

483
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:01,399
What do you think?

484
00:40:01,899 --> 00:40:03,776
Don't the three of you look similar?

485
00:40:03,859 --> 00:40:04,860
Yeah.

486
00:40:07,863 --> 00:40:08,989
Seo-jun.

487
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:11,409
Your mom and dad

488
00:40:12,326 --> 00:40:14,870
loved you very much.

489
00:40:15,996 --> 00:40:17,248
By the way,

490
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:21,794
why did Mom and Dad go to heaven?

491
00:40:23,879 --> 00:40:25,548
There was an accident.

492
00:40:26,715 --> 00:40:28,717
Your parents got hurt a lot.

493
00:40:30,469 --> 00:40:32,638
They went somewhere
where they won't be hurt anymore.

494
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,227
- Mom.
- Yes?

495
00:40:38,310 --> 00:40:40,980
Does it mean that I have two moms?

496
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,531
Right.

497
00:40:50,614 --> 00:40:52,575
You have two moms.

498
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,160
You also have a dad.

499
00:40:56,078 --> 00:40:57,621
They may not be with you,

500
00:40:57,705 --> 00:40:59,832
but if you remember them,

501
00:41:00,416 --> 00:41:01,667
they'll be with you.

502
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:03,961
Okay.

503
00:41:04,753 --> 00:41:06,130
Mom.

504
00:41:06,213 --> 00:41:07,882
Thank you for raising me.

505
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:18,142
Seo-jun.

506
00:41:22,980 --> 00:41:25,858
I love you very much.

507
00:41:25,941 --> 00:41:28,611
I love you too, Mom.

508
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:22,456
Why are you still at work?

509
00:42:22,957 --> 00:42:23,874
Hey.

510
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:25,251
Why didn't you go home?

511
00:42:25,334 --> 00:42:26,752
Is something wrong?

512
00:42:26,835 --> 00:42:29,255
I don't come here
only when something's wrong.

513
00:42:29,338 --> 00:42:31,882
I had a meeting nearby,
and I thought of you.

514
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:33,342
Is everything really okay?

515
00:42:33,425 --> 00:42:34,927
Are things okay with Chairman Woo?

516
00:42:35,010 --> 00:42:36,845
Of course, same as always.

517
00:42:36,929 --> 00:42:39,181
He still doesn't like me.

518
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:43,060
Got a lot to do?

519
00:42:45,104 --> 00:42:48,190
A lot happened during the day.
I needed some time to think.

520
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:49,984
What is it about?

521
00:42:52,570 --> 00:42:53,571
It's <i>Rainbow Bingsu</i>.

522
00:42:53,654 --> 00:42:55,239
It's Ms. Jung's book.

523
00:42:55,322 --> 00:42:56,490
It's by Seo-jun's mother.

524
00:42:57,324 --> 00:43:00,160
Wait, do you know Seo-jun's mother?

525
00:43:02,371 --> 00:43:04,707
Oh, well…

526
00:43:05,249 --> 00:43:07,626
I've met her a few times.

527
00:43:10,212 --> 00:43:11,213
Why?

528
00:43:11,714 --> 00:43:13,507
Did something happen to Seo-jun?

529
00:43:19,972 --> 00:43:21,599
She must have a lot on her mind.

530
00:43:28,522 --> 00:43:29,940
WRITER JUNG SU-HYEON

531
00:43:36,322 --> 00:43:38,282
<i>What are you doing right now?</i>

532
00:43:38,365 --> 00:43:39,366
What?

533
00:43:55,883 --> 00:43:57,009
Are you okay?

534
00:43:57,092 --> 00:43:58,302
You came.

535
00:43:59,261 --> 00:44:01,764
I'm sorry for calling you so suddenly.

536
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:04,141
It's just that

537
00:44:05,059 --> 00:44:06,935
I had no one else to talk to.

538
00:44:10,564 --> 00:44:13,233
How did you know that was my expertise?

