00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:15,444
Say everything you want to say.

540
00:44:15,527 --> 00:44:17,905
I'm a good listener.

541
00:44:17,988 --> 00:44:20,532
I'm a pro-listener, you know?

542
00:44:22,701 --> 00:44:24,119
I miss my sister.

543
00:44:25,829 --> 00:44:29,667
I just miss my sister a lot today.

544
00:44:34,755 --> 00:44:36,006
Su-jin.

545
00:44:37,424 --> 00:44:39,259
Am I doing a good job?

546
00:44:44,556 --> 00:44:45,766
Didn't you just hear it?

547
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:48,018
She said you're doing very well.

548
00:44:55,526 --> 00:44:58,278
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to make you cry.

549
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:00,364
Don't be sorry.

550
00:45:25,139 --> 00:45:26,140
It's okay.

551
00:45:40,988 --> 00:45:43,115
HEADHUNTING WORK CONTRACT

552
00:45:44,116 --> 00:45:46,326
I'm sorry for making you wait.

553
00:45:46,410 --> 00:45:48,579
Don't be. I prefer to make it clear.

554
00:45:48,662 --> 00:45:50,330
You accepted my request.

555
00:45:50,414 --> 00:45:53,459
It shows that my company can be trusted.

556
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:55,544
You must be quite busy.

557
00:45:55,627 --> 00:45:57,921
I saw many articles
about Ikonic Biotechnology.

558
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,173
Yes, it's hard to keep up.

559
00:45:59,756 --> 00:46:01,216
With the sudden increase in size,

560
00:46:01,300 --> 00:46:04,553
I feel anxious and puzzled
at the same time.

561
00:46:04,636 --> 00:46:08,223
You're being rewarded for your
long commitment to develop the new drug.

562
00:46:09,266 --> 00:46:11,143
Speaking of which,

563
00:46:11,226 --> 00:46:14,938
could Peoplez exclusively take charge
of hiring our personnel?

564
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:17,065
The company will keep getting bigger.

565
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:21,069
I'm a researcher stuck in the lab all day,
so I'm hopeless in this field.

566
00:46:21,153 --> 00:46:25,324
It's hard to estimate how many more
employees I need to hire.

567
00:46:25,407 --> 00:46:29,036
If Peoplez takes charge
of searching for our future employees,

568
00:46:29,119 --> 00:46:30,787
I'll give you a share in my company.

569
00:46:30,871 --> 00:46:34,166
As you know, the value could grow
exponentially if we go public.

570
00:46:34,249 --> 00:46:37,711
Think of it as growing
with a company with potential.

571
00:46:38,545 --> 00:46:39,588
Please accept my offer.

572
00:46:40,964 --> 00:46:42,299
Thank you for the offer.

573
00:46:42,382 --> 00:46:43,550
I'll think about it.

574
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:44,676
Sure.

575
00:46:53,018 --> 00:46:54,269
Mr. Kim.

576
00:46:54,353 --> 00:46:55,729
Hey, Mr. Yu.

577
00:46:56,230 --> 00:46:57,272
Is something wrong?

578
00:46:58,565 --> 00:47:00,984
I'm not sure about it,

579
00:47:01,068 --> 00:47:03,111
but I can't get it off my mind.

580
00:47:04,530 --> 00:47:06,240
Changing the direction

581
00:47:06,323 --> 00:47:07,658
- might be okay.
- It's good.

582
00:47:07,741 --> 00:47:09,201
This coffee…

583
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:10,744
My friend is working at NEXT.

584
00:47:10,827 --> 00:47:13,205
That's why I'm very interested…

585
00:47:13,288 --> 00:47:16,041
Why is Jeong-nam with Sung-woong?

586
00:47:16,124 --> 00:47:17,668
It could work.

587
00:47:19,044 --> 00:47:21,838
- Mr. Kim, what are you doing?
- It's nothing. I'm coming.

588
00:47:21,922 --> 00:47:24,424
Now that we met up, I wanted to ask…

589
00:47:24,508 --> 00:47:27,886
Were Jeong-nam and Sung-woong close?

590
00:47:27,970 --> 00:47:29,012
I'm not sure. Why?

591
00:47:29,805 --> 00:47:31,056
Oh, it's nothing.

592
00:47:31,139 --> 00:47:32,683
Let's go.

593
00:47:32,766 --> 00:47:34,851
He used to work here?

594
00:47:35,686 --> 00:47:36,895
Yes, his name is Go Jeong-nam.

595
00:47:36,979 --> 00:47:40,524
After our project with NEXT became public,
he contacted me and we met up.

596
00:47:40,607 --> 00:47:42,985
Since then, he kept asking questions.

597
00:47:43,569 --> 00:47:46,071
It made me uncomfortable,
so I ignored his calls.

598
00:47:46,154 --> 00:47:49,032
He definitely told me
that he left this field.

599
00:47:49,950 --> 00:47:52,828
If he keeps seeing employees from Peoplez,

600
00:47:52,911 --> 00:47:54,413
he must have an ulterior motive.

601
00:47:54,496 --> 00:47:55,914
- Right?
- Yes.

602
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:58,875
Did he contact you right after
the article about NEXT got published?

603
00:47:59,459 --> 00:48:01,878
The one who needs information
related to that the most…

604
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:04,881
Career Way.

605
00:48:05,882 --> 00:48:09,136
Could it be why their candidates
overlapped with ours?

606
00:48:11,638 --> 00:48:12,889
I'll find out.

607
00:48:12,973 --> 00:48:15,392
- Did you say anything else?
- No.

608
00:48:15,475 --> 00:48:16,685
I'm not that stupid.

609
00:48:16,768 --> 00:48:20,439
I read that Peoplez is in charge
of finding a CEO for NEXT.

610
00:48:20,522 --> 00:48:24,526
Instead of those formerly in management,
people like lawyers and journalists…

611
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:26,820
No, I can't.

612
00:48:26,903 --> 00:48:28,280
It's a trade secret.

613
00:48:31,783 --> 00:48:32,909
Mr. Yu.

614
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:38,332
I think I made a mistake.

615
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:43,462
Dong-gi, it's me. Can you do me a favor?

616
00:48:43,545 --> 00:48:46,465
Can you make a request to Career Way?
Like it's from Hansu Electronics.

617
00:48:47,466 --> 00:48:49,009
You're amazing. Thanks.

618
00:48:52,929 --> 00:48:56,642
Ms. Kang, I verified that
Go Jeong-nam works at Career Way.

619
00:48:56,725 --> 00:49:00,604
Does it mean Jeong-nam has been
stealing information on our candidates?

620
00:49:01,563 --> 00:49:05,651
And he approached Mr.
Kim to steal information?

621
00:49:09,571 --> 00:49:10,989
I'm sorry, Ms. Kang.

622
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:13,533
I know people can't be trusted,

623
00:49:13,617 --> 00:49:15,327
but I didn't expect this.

624
00:49:15,410 --> 00:49:17,704
I treated Jeong-nam so well.

625
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:18,955
How could he betray me?

626
00:49:19,039 --> 00:49:22,959
Did he take our database
when he left Peoplez?

627
00:49:24,252 --> 00:49:26,880
Ms. Kang, we shouldn't let him
get away with this.

628
00:49:27,839 --> 00:49:30,008
We need to come up with a new plan.

629
00:49:35,889 --> 00:49:38,141
- Jeong-nam.
- Mr. Kim.

630
00:49:38,225 --> 00:49:39,935
I'm sorry for being so late.

631
00:49:40,018 --> 00:49:41,269
It's okay.

632
00:49:41,353 --> 00:49:42,979
- Sit down.
- Okay.

633
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,399
The meeting took longer than I thought.

634
00:49:46,108 --> 00:49:47,984
As it's an important project,

635
00:49:48,985 --> 00:49:51,530
it's not easy to decide on the candidates.

636
00:49:52,656 --> 00:49:55,492
So have the candidates been decided?

637
00:49:56,410 --> 00:49:58,495
Yes, they've been decided.

638
00:49:59,204 --> 00:50:01,748
Mr. Kim, would you like
something cool to drink?

639
00:50:01,832 --> 00:50:02,791
If it's on you.

640
00:50:02,874 --> 00:50:04,084
- I'll buy you a drink.
- Wait.

641
00:50:04,167 --> 00:50:06,044
Before that, I need to go to the restroom.

642
00:50:06,128 --> 00:50:08,046
Actually, I'll take my time.

643
00:50:08,130 --> 00:50:11,508
I was worried about being late to see you,
I didn't have a chance to go.

644
00:50:11,591 --> 00:50:12,926
I'll be right back.

645
00:50:25,439 --> 00:50:27,858
Way to go, Mr. Kim.

646
00:50:29,025 --> 00:50:31,319
Information on our candidates
was handed over to Career Way.

647
00:50:32,112 --> 00:50:35,323
So they think that
it's our final list of candidates?

648
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,784
Serves them right for cheating.

649
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:38,952
This feels satisfying.

650
00:50:39,035 --> 00:50:41,997
Shall we start discussing
our real list of candidates?

651
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:43,373
Yes, ma'am.

652
00:50:43,457 --> 00:50:46,168
We'll start searching for candidates
from the beginning today.

653
00:50:51,923 --> 00:50:53,425
"Resignation rate at NEXT?"

654
00:50:53,508 --> 00:50:56,011
People often change jobs and resign
in this field.

655
00:50:56,094 --> 00:50:58,138
While taking that into consideration,

656
00:50:58,221 --> 00:51:01,141
it'd be worthwhile to take a look
at the resignation rate graph.

657
00:51:01,224 --> 00:51:03,935
At NEXT, people with
the highest resignation rate are

658
00:51:04,019 --> 00:51:06,730
managers and senior managers
of five and ten years.

659
00:51:06,813 --> 00:51:09,608
The most important middle tier at NEXT.

660
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:12,360
The essential workers left the company,

661
00:51:12,444 --> 00:51:13,737
and only old-timers remain?

662
00:51:13,820 --> 00:51:15,947
Yes, centered around a CEO
with a programming background,

663
00:51:16,031 --> 00:51:19,075
there came about a discrimination
against nonprogrammers.

664
00:51:19,159 --> 00:51:22,162
The executives are only interested
in keeping their positions.

665
00:51:24,331 --> 00:51:25,165
Hey,

666
00:51:25,248 --> 00:51:26,458
who do you think will be our new CEO?

667
00:51:26,541 --> 00:51:27,793
Will they do it right this time?

668
00:51:27,876 --> 00:51:29,169
That has nothing to do with it.

669
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:32,214
I just hope our workplace politics
won't scare him away.

670
00:51:32,297 --> 00:51:34,883
- Do you know who I pity the most?
- Who?

671
00:51:34,966 --> 00:51:37,052
You and me who get ignored
for not being programmers.

672
00:51:37,135 --> 00:51:39,221
But we can't even resign.

673
00:51:40,013 --> 00:51:41,139
Hey, hey.

674
00:51:43,809 --> 00:51:45,227
- Let's go.
- Come on.

675
00:51:47,020 --> 00:51:49,105
<i>When employees are saying that,</i>

676
00:51:49,189 --> 00:51:51,566
it means that things are rotten
at the workplace.

677
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:54,444
The real crisis at NEXT
may not be external,

678
00:51:54,528 --> 00:51:55,987
but internal.

679
00:51:56,071 --> 00:52:00,575
It might be better to search candidates
from the employees' perspective.

680
00:52:00,659 --> 00:52:02,828
What eventually changes the company

681
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:05,205
is its employees.

682
00:52:06,665 --> 00:52:07,833
That's all I have.

683
00:52:10,252 --> 00:52:12,546
From now on, we'll be focusing

684
00:52:12,629 --> 00:52:14,339
on NEXT's internal crisis.

685
00:52:14,422 --> 00:52:16,132
We'll start from the beginning

686
00:52:16,216 --> 00:52:19,469
and find the real problem at NEXT
from the employees' perspective.

687
00:52:19,553 --> 00:52:20,428
SEARCHING REVIEWS ON COMPANY

688
00:52:20,512 --> 00:52:21,429
NEXT

689
00:52:22,055 --> 00:52:23,515
"COMPARED TO THE SIZE,
LACK OF SOLIDARITY AT WORK"

690
00:52:23,598 --> 00:52:25,433
"AT NEXT,
ONLY BROWNNOSERS GET PROMOTED"

691
00:52:25,517 --> 00:52:28,186
"PROGRAMMERS
GET SPECIAL TREATMENT"

692
00:52:34,192 --> 00:52:35,861
They lost everyone who's competent.

693
00:52:35,944 --> 00:52:37,195
Talkers.

694
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:40,490
Only those who know how to talk
remain in high positions.

695
00:52:40,574 --> 00:52:43,410
Darn it.
Could you find me a new job instead?

696
00:52:44,703 --> 00:52:45,996
Cooperation? Ha!

697
00:52:46,079 --> 00:52:48,123
I can't even talk with programmers.

698
00:52:48,206 --> 00:52:50,208
I only do what I get paid for.

699
00:52:50,292 --> 00:52:52,460
Not like I get paid more for working hard.

700
00:52:53,336 --> 00:52:56,590
Won't it be better with a new CEO?

701
00:52:57,841 --> 00:53:02,387
Wouldn't it be great
to get rid of all the old-timers?

702
00:53:02,470 --> 00:53:04,264
Look how naive he is.

703
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:06,266
Want in on a secret?

704
00:53:07,183 --> 00:53:09,686
A new CEO has already been decided.

705
00:53:09,769 --> 00:53:11,813
Again, it's someone to their liking.

706
00:53:11,897 --> 00:53:14,274
Management at NEXT is so predictable.

707
00:53:14,357 --> 00:53:15,442
Just drink.

708
00:53:15,525 --> 00:53:17,986
If you don't mind me asking,
could you tell me

709
00:53:18,069 --> 00:53:21,656
what you consider
as the most important in management?

710
00:53:22,991 --> 00:53:24,117
That's a hard question.

711
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:25,911
I don't know if it answers your question,

712
00:53:25,994 --> 00:53:29,831
but on my first day at work,
there's something that I always do.

713
00:53:34,294 --> 00:53:37,005
Ms. Kang,
what do you think of this candidate?

714
00:53:37,088 --> 00:53:39,466
He has enough experience
in human resources.

715
00:53:40,508 --> 00:53:42,719
He doesn't have much field experience.

716
00:53:42,802 --> 00:53:44,471
What about this candidate?

717
00:53:44,554 --> 00:53:47,891
He had the highest score from
his co-workers during reference checks.

718
00:53:47,974 --> 00:53:51,269
He leads his team
with flexibility and gentle leadership.

719
00:53:51,353 --> 00:53:53,772
Gyu-rim's candidate is known
to be very competent.

720
00:53:53,855 --> 00:53:56,441
But, if I can suggest one more person,

721
00:53:56,524 --> 00:53:58,777
NEXT needs to pull out rotten weeds.

722
00:53:58,860 --> 00:54:01,237
It should be someone who's determined.

723
00:54:39,859 --> 00:54:41,111
I feel much better now.

724
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:46,616
Shall we get some fresh air?

725
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:05,093
I want to stay like this for ten minutes.

726
00:55:06,886 --> 00:55:09,097
It's almost over, isn't it?

727
00:55:09,180 --> 00:55:10,140
Yes.

728
00:55:10,807 --> 00:55:12,350
You worked really hard.

729
00:55:12,934 --> 00:55:14,477
You too, Ji-yun.

730
00:55:16,062 --> 00:55:18,815
If the project is successful,
shall we go on a trip?

731
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:20,817
A trip?

732
00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:23,069
Where?

733
00:55:23,153 --> 00:55:25,864
Anywhere.
Is there somewhere you want to go?

734
00:55:27,782 --> 00:55:28,867
The sea.

735
00:55:28,950 --> 00:55:31,244
I haven't been to the sea in a long time.

736
00:55:31,327 --> 00:55:32,912
The sea sounds great.

737
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:34,873
Is there anywhere else you want to go?

738
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:39,461
Tell me. Be it the mountains,
or even outer space.

739
00:55:40,086 --> 00:55:41,588
- Outer space?
- Yes.

740
00:55:43,048 --> 00:55:44,632
Ms. Kang, are you here?

741
00:55:47,802 --> 00:55:49,679
Gyu-rim, what is it?

742
00:55:49,763 --> 00:55:51,681
There you are.

743
00:55:51,765 --> 00:55:53,308
Is Mr. Yu with you?

744
00:55:53,391 --> 00:55:55,310
No, I'm here alone.

745
00:55:56,144 --> 00:55:57,645
He isn't with you?

746
00:55:58,146 --> 00:56:00,982
What? Isn't he at his desk?

747
00:56:01,066 --> 00:56:03,234
No, he isn't. Did he go somewhere?

748
00:56:03,318 --> 00:56:05,111
Maybe he went to the restroom.

749
00:56:05,904 --> 00:56:06,780
That's strange.

750
00:56:06,863 --> 00:56:09,240
I thought I heard his voice here.

751
00:56:09,324 --> 00:56:12,077
