796
00:58:50,777 --> 00:58:54,113
managers prioritizing their position
over doing actual work,

797
00:58:54,197 --> 00:58:57,951
and a lack of trust and loyalty
from the employees.

798
00:58:58,535 --> 00:59:00,161
The real crisis at NEXT is…

799
00:59:00,245 --> 00:59:01,412
COMPANY REVIEW ON NEXT

800
00:59:01,496 --> 00:59:03,748
…internal, not external.

801
00:59:03,831 --> 00:59:06,834
I'm sure none of you can deny it.

802
00:59:12,632 --> 00:59:14,092
<i>What eventually changes the company</i>

803
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:16,094
is its employees.

804
00:59:18,263 --> 00:59:20,223
What leads NEXT
with a sense of responsibility

805
00:59:20,306 --> 00:59:21,683
isn't external assessments.

806
00:59:21,766 --> 00:59:25,812
It's those who currently work at NEXT.

807
00:59:26,396 --> 00:59:28,022
To truly benefit NEXT,

808
00:59:28,106 --> 00:59:30,024
please select carefully

809
00:59:30,108 --> 00:59:31,901
the most appropriate CEO.

810
00:59:53,423 --> 00:59:57,302
<i>The new CEO at the web portal NEXT</i>
<i>has been decided.</i>

811
00:59:57,385 --> 00:59:59,095
<i>Newly appointed CEO Jung Su-hwan stated</i>

812
00:59:59,178 --> 01:00:02,265
<i>bringing stability to the company</i>
<i>as the number one priority.</i>

813
01:00:02,348 --> 01:00:03,725
<i>He added what leads NEXT's future</i>

814
01:00:03,808 --> 01:00:07,729
<i>will be supportive company culture</i>
<i>and employee growth.</i>

815
01:00:07,812 --> 01:00:11,983
"Also, the new CEO at NEXT was appointed

816
01:00:12,066 --> 01:00:15,695
through a search firm called Peoplez!"

817
01:00:18,239 --> 01:00:19,824
Eun-ho!

818
01:00:19,907 --> 01:00:20,950
Good job.

819
01:00:21,034 --> 01:00:22,744
Well done!

820
01:00:22,827 --> 01:00:25,204
Now, we're the exclusive headhunter
for NEXT, right?

821
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:28,750
The total number of employees
at NEXT is about 4,000.

822
01:00:28,833 --> 01:00:30,376
It's 4,000 people!

823
01:00:30,460 --> 01:00:32,712
Is it just me? I can't believe it.

824
01:00:32,795 --> 01:00:33,838
- You can't believe it?
- No.

825
01:00:33,921 --> 01:00:35,840
I can't believe it either.
What should we do?

826
01:00:35,923 --> 01:00:38,468
We must go out on a company dinner
to believe it!

827
01:00:38,551 --> 01:00:39,636
A company dinner.

828
01:00:39,719 --> 01:00:40,803
Mr. Kim.

829
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:42,805
He brought it up so naturally.

830
01:00:42,889 --> 01:00:44,682
What's wrong? A company dinner.

831
01:00:46,434 --> 01:00:47,602
A company dinner!

832
01:00:51,147 --> 01:00:51,981
Goodness.

833
01:00:59,781 --> 01:01:00,907
Let's go.

834
01:01:01,491 --> 01:01:03,701
She gave us the corporate card!

835
01:01:03,785 --> 01:01:06,329
- Ms. Kang!
- I made this happen, guys!

836
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:08,623
- Is everyone in?
- What should we eat?

837
01:01:08,706 --> 01:01:11,584
We can get something big
with the black card.

838
01:01:11,668 --> 01:01:13,378
I'd love some dakgalbi!

839
01:01:15,129 --> 01:01:16,172
Enjoy your food.

840
01:01:16,255 --> 01:01:18,132
It's on us, so enjoy.

841
01:01:21,302 --> 01:01:23,304
Gosh, it looks delicious.

842
01:01:23,388 --> 01:01:25,765
- Come on, Mr. Kim.
- What?

843
01:01:25,848 --> 01:01:29,143
At times like these, you should be QSPN
and move out the way.

844
01:01:29,227 --> 01:01:30,728
QSPN? What's that?

845
01:01:30,812 --> 01:01:33,398
Have you stopped updating your notes?

846
01:01:33,481 --> 01:01:35,233
Am I the only one who doesn't know?

847
01:01:35,316 --> 01:01:36,401
At times like these,

848
01:01:36,484 --> 01:01:40,154
be quick, smart, and polite to notice.

849
01:01:40,238 --> 01:01:41,614
What do you want me to do?

850
01:01:42,365 --> 01:01:44,033
Please get up and change seats.

851
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:45,702
Mr. Yu, come this way.

852
01:01:46,828 --> 01:01:48,079
- Goodness.
- This way, please.

853
01:01:48,162 --> 01:01:50,039
- Mr. Yu, over here.
- Come this way.

854
01:01:51,124 --> 01:01:51,958
Hurry over here.

855
01:01:52,041 --> 01:01:54,585
- That's good.
- You're being so slow.

856
01:01:54,669 --> 01:01:56,129
And here's my bestie.

857
01:01:57,088 --> 01:01:59,173
They didn't tell us about it,
but I'm still jealous.

858
01:01:59,257 --> 01:02:00,717
- Who wants soju?
- Me!

859
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,719
- Cheers.
- Mr. Kim.

860
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:08,808
Have you tried this?

861
01:02:08,891 --> 01:02:10,184
It looks delicious.

862
01:02:11,310 --> 01:02:12,603
Why is this so tender?

863
01:02:12,687 --> 01:02:14,939
- Kyung-hwa.
- When it's this tender,

864
01:02:15,022 --> 01:02:16,149
I need a drink.

865
01:02:16,899 --> 01:02:19,277
We should drink at a time like this.

866
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:25,867
Drinking never felt so easy.

867
01:02:26,451 --> 01:02:28,453
Kwang-hee, let's liven up the mood.

868
01:02:28,536 --> 01:02:30,204
Okay, I'll make us drinks.

869
01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:31,372
Give me your glasses.

870
01:02:31,456 --> 01:02:33,082
- Hand them over.
- Sit back down.

871
01:02:33,166 --> 01:02:34,041
What?

872
01:02:34,709 --> 01:02:36,127
Sit back down.

873
01:02:36,210 --> 01:02:37,378
Sit? Okay.

874
01:02:41,257 --> 01:02:43,342
She must be showing us a new trick.

875
01:03:03,279 --> 01:03:04,238
She's a pro.

876
01:03:06,407 --> 01:03:07,742
What was that about?

877
01:03:08,451 --> 01:03:10,661
I don't like the drinks you make.

878
01:03:10,745 --> 01:03:11,871
You should've told me before.

879
01:03:11,954 --> 01:03:13,831
Gyu-rim, who exactly are you?

880
01:03:15,166 --> 01:03:16,250
All right!

881
01:03:16,334 --> 01:03:18,085
Attention, everyone.

882
01:03:18,169 --> 01:03:22,256
This is a special event to celebrate
the success of our project

883
01:03:22,340 --> 01:03:25,551
and also to promote companionship

884
01:03:25,635 --> 01:03:28,137
among all the employees.

885
01:03:28,221 --> 01:03:29,222
Today…

886
01:03:30,056 --> 01:03:32,350
- One more time!
- Don't do that.

887
01:03:32,433 --> 01:03:34,101
- Drink until the end!
- Stop it.

888
01:03:34,185 --> 01:03:35,436
Oh, please!

889
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:37,396
Also, Ms. Kang.

890
01:03:37,939 --> 01:03:41,943
To commemorate your joining
the company dinner voluntarily,

891
01:03:42,026 --> 01:03:43,569
- a speech, please.
- A speech? No way.

892
01:03:43,653 --> 01:03:45,238
- I don't want to.
- Come on, Ms. Kang.

893
01:03:45,321 --> 01:03:47,281
- No way. Please.
- Ms. Kang!

894
01:03:47,365 --> 01:03:50,034
Quiet down. As you all know,

895
01:03:50,117 --> 01:03:52,703
this makes her embarrassed.

896
01:03:53,538 --> 01:03:54,997
CEO Kang!

897
01:03:55,957 --> 01:03:57,250
- CEO Kang!
- CEO Kang!

898
01:03:57,333 --> 01:03:58,668
- CEO Kang!
- CEO Kang!

899
01:03:58,751 --> 01:04:00,002
- CEO Kang!
- CEO Kang!

900
01:04:00,711 --> 01:04:01,921
Enough!

901
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:07,301
Let's work hard again starting tomorrow.

902
01:04:09,220 --> 01:04:11,556
- Gosh.
- I don't think I can.

903
01:04:11,639 --> 01:04:12,765
What's wrong with her?

904
01:04:16,185 --> 01:04:18,980
The project was successful

905
01:04:19,063 --> 01:04:20,356
thanks to all of you.

906
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:22,191
Thank you.

907
01:04:25,361 --> 01:04:26,404
What's going on?

908
01:04:30,408 --> 01:04:32,618
Enjoy the food tonight.

909
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:33,995
Let's have fun.

910
01:04:34,078 --> 01:04:35,079
Cheers.

911
01:04:35,746 --> 01:04:38,040
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

912
01:04:39,083 --> 01:04:40,376
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

913
01:04:40,459 --> 01:04:41,419
You grew up well.

914
01:04:41,502 --> 01:04:42,753
Shut up and eat.

915
01:04:45,673 --> 01:04:47,675
Have you thought about
what to do about your job?

916
01:04:49,260 --> 01:04:50,845
Has that been troubling you?

917
01:04:51,846 --> 01:04:53,097
Of course.

918
01:04:53,180 --> 01:04:55,057
It's something that concerns you.

919
01:04:58,477 --> 01:05:03,816
I'd like you to work
where your competence can shine more.

920
01:05:05,902 --> 01:05:07,653
Don't I shine at this company?

921
01:05:07,737 --> 01:05:09,363
I'm starting to feel disappointed.

922
01:05:10,239 --> 01:05:11,824
You know that's not what I mean.

923
01:05:13,534 --> 01:05:17,163
I realized it once again
during our project on NEXT.

924
01:05:18,372 --> 01:05:21,250
It'd be greedy of me to keep
a talented person like you

925
01:05:21,334 --> 01:05:22,543
all to myself.

926
01:05:23,461 --> 01:05:26,464
Wow, you finally acknowledge me, Ms. Kang.

927
01:05:26,547 --> 01:05:28,674
You're getting arrogant already.

928
01:05:31,594 --> 01:05:32,595
Anyway,

929
01:05:33,429 --> 01:05:34,847
don't worry about me.

930
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:38,184
Make the best decision for yourself.

931
01:05:44,815 --> 01:05:46,233
Okay.

932
01:05:46,317 --> 01:05:47,568
I'll think about it.

933
01:05:50,446 --> 01:05:51,489
It feels warm.

934
01:05:51,989 --> 01:05:53,866
Your hand fits right in.

935
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:55,618
You just have big hands.

936
01:06:14,929 --> 01:06:17,932
YOU HAVE NEW MESSAGES

937
01:06:31,654 --> 01:06:34,532
<i>Ms. Kang, there are many articles</i>
<i>assuming that it's Peoplez.</i>

938
01:06:34,615 --> 01:06:35,866
<i>Is it true?</i>

939
01:06:36,409 --> 01:06:39,954
IKONIC BIOTECHNOLOGY, FRAUD
OF 20 BILLION WON… CEO VANISHED

940
01:07:12,278 --> 01:07:14,321
Ms. Kang, is it true
that Peoplez was involved?

941
01:07:21,704 --> 01:07:24,081
Ms. Kang, is it true
that Peoplez was involved?

942
01:07:24,165 --> 01:07:25,541
Were you not aware of it?

943
01:07:25,624 --> 01:07:27,376
Did you recommend the candidate
while knowing?

944
01:07:27,460 --> 01:07:29,253
What will happen to those
hired by the company?

945
01:07:29,336 --> 01:07:31,172
Were you not aware at all?

946
01:07:31,255 --> 01:07:33,466
- I changed jobs because I trusted you.
- What do I do?

947
01:07:33,549 --> 01:07:34,675
- Ms. Kang!
- How could you?

948
01:07:34,759 --> 01:07:35,926
<i>She came here?</i>

949
01:07:36,010 --> 01:07:37,636
<i>- The CEO…</i>
<i>- How dare she show up here?</i>

950
01:07:37,720 --> 01:07:39,013
<i>She's a murderer.</i>

951
01:07:39,096 --> 01:07:41,557
- Don't you know his whereabouts?
- Since when did this happen?

952
01:07:41,640 --> 01:07:43,100
Anything to say to the victims?

953
01:07:43,184 --> 01:07:45,436
Do you have anything to say?

954
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:55,714
We'll be conducting a search and seizure
of the office.

955
01:08:55,798 --> 01:08:57,341
Why are you lowering the blinds?

956
01:08:57,424 --> 01:08:58,342
Ms. Kang isn't a criminal!

957
01:08:58,425 --> 01:09:00,219
<i>Why are you doing this to me?</i>

958
01:09:00,302 --> 01:09:01,137
<i>Because I hate you.</i>

959
01:09:01,220 --> 01:09:03,931
<i>Career Way will take over Peoplez.</i>

960
01:09:04,014 --> 01:09:04,849
Was it you, Father?

961
01:09:04,932 --> 01:09:06,142
I'm figuring out what to do.

962
01:09:06,225 --> 01:09:08,894
If I expect it to be a loss,
I'd need to make a decision.

963
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:09,854
Are you okay?

964
01:09:09,937 --> 01:09:11,438
You won't have to worry about Mr. Yu.

965
01:09:11,522 --> 01:09:12,439
I mean, you.

966
01:09:12,523 --> 01:09:13,566
Are you okay, Jeong-hoon?

967
01:09:13,649 --> 01:09:15,109
Ji-yun, you aren't alone.

968
01:09:15,192 --> 01:09:17,486
You weren't and won't be going forth.

969
01:09:17,570 --> 01:09:19,321
<i>I hated my life.</i>

970
01:09:19,405 --> 01:09:20,906
- Good morning.
- You came to work early.

971
01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:23,284
<i>- Ever since I met you,</i>
- Hello!

972
01:09:23,367 --> 01:09:24,994
<i>I started to like myself.</i>

973
01:09:25,077 --> 01:09:30,082
